`settings` | Key-value config for janitor / provider settings. | Manual or migration-managed |\n\n  Line 321: | `importance` | 1–5; `5` opts a global memory into every-session injection |\n\n  Line 322: | `confidence` | 0.0–1.0; reserved for janitor / promotion logic |\n\n  Line 325: | `status` | `active` / `pending` / `deprecated` / `superseded` — soft-delete + supersession |\n\n  Line 328: | `superseded_by`, `superseded_at` | Pointer to the memory that replaced this one (audit trail) |\n\n  Line 439: context at session start, (b) survive compaction without state loss, (c) record\n\n  Line 440: progress at session end, and (d) propose learnings post-session. MCP tools cover the\n\n  Line 444: `SessionStart`, `PreCompact`, `EvaluateSession`, `UpdateContext`. Hooks are\n\n  Line 450: - **MCP-only.** Rejected. There is no MCP equivalent to \"this is a fresh session,\n\n  Line 452:   `context` at every session start — defeats J1 and US-1.\n\n  Line 456: - **Polling cron.** Rejected. Not aligned with session boundaries; can't inject at\n\n  Line 467: - (–) Four hook processes per session add some startup latency; offset by Bun's\n\n  Line 531: - **Stored decay score updated on a schedule.** Rejected for v1. Adds a janitor\n\n  Line 546: - (–) Importance must be set correctly by the user / EvaluateSession or the model\n\n  Line 601:   For four hooks per session this matters. Also requires `better-sqlite3` native\n\n  Line 639: **Symptom.** Two Claude Code sessions starting in different cwds at the same time\n\n  Line 670: janitor; use it in `ORDER BY`. Trade write amplification for read latency.\n\n  Line 680: **Direction.** Add an `events` table (append-only): event_type, latency_ms,\n\n  Line 710: ### W9 — No memory provenance\n\n  Line 715: **Direction.** Add a `provenance` table or columns: source_type\n\n  Line 716: (`session` / `git-backfill` / `manual` / `evaluate`), source_ref (session id, SHA,\n\n  Line 719: ### W10 — `EvaluateSession` policy is unclear\n\n  Lin