{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780925754251,"sessionID":"ses_158903c2bffeCx3bRrBHJwKOQa","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5nSbFaDeqJIBG6ly2OZKowDj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/governance/scope-governance.ts","offset":227,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/governance/scope-governance.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n227:  * All ingest mutation surfaces should call `validateGovernedIngest` with their\n228:  * available metadata before writes or job enqueue. When any scope,\n229:  * provenance, governed timestamp, or retention field is present,\n230:  * `provenanceActor` is mandatory so audit rows can identify the caller.\n231:  *\n232:  * @param input - Candidate ingest metadata.\n233:  * @returns `true` when governance or scope metadata requires enforcement.\n234:  */\n235: export function requiresGovernedIngest(input: GovernedIngestInput): boolean {\n236:   const scope = normalizeScopeContext(input);\n237:   return Object.values(scope).some((value) => typeof value === 'string')\n238:     || typeof input.provenanceSource === 'string'\n239:     || typeof input.provenanceActor === 'string'\n240:     || typeof input.governedAt === 'string'\n241:     || (input.retentionPolicy !== 'ephemeral' && typeof input.deleteAfter === 'string');\n242: }\n243: \n244: /**\n245:  * Validate governed-ingest metadata and return normalized persistence fields.\n246:  *\n247:  * @param input - Candidate ingest metadata.\n248:  * @returns Validation result with normalized scope, provenance, and retention data.\n249:  */\n250: export function validateGovernedIngest(input: GovernedIngestInput): GovernanceDecision {\n251:   const scope = normalizeScopeContext(input);\n252:   const issues: string[] = [];\n253:   const governedAt = normalizeIsoTimestamp(input.governedAt) ?? new Date().toISOString();\n254:   const deleteAfter = normalizeIsoTimestamp(input.deleteAfter) ?? null;\n255:   const retentionPolicy: RetentionPolicy = input.retentionPolicy === 'ephemeral'\n256:     ? input.retentionPolicy\n257:     : 'keep';\n258:   const provenanceSource = normalizeId(input.provenanceSource) ?? '';\n259:   const provenanceActor = normalizeId(input.provenanceActor) ?? '';\n260: \n261:   if (!requiresGovernedIngest(input)) {\n262:     const computedDeleteAfter = deleteAfter ?? (\n263:       retentionPolicy === 'ephemeral'\n264:         ? new Date(Date.now() + DEFAULT_EPHEMERAL_TTL_MS).toISOString()\n265:         : null\n266:     );\n267:     // B8: Return null instead of empty string for optional scope fields\n268:     // when governance is not required, to avoid persisting false-y placeholders.\n269:     return {\n270:       allowed: true,\n271:       normalized: {\n272:         tenantId: scope.tenantId || null,\n273:         userId: scope.userId || null,\n274:         agentId: scope.agentId || null,\n275:         sessionId: scope.sessionId || null,\n276:         provenanceSource: provenanceSource || null,\n277:         provenanceActor: provenanceActor || null,\n278:         governedAt,\n279:         retentionPolicy,\n280:         deleteAfter: computedDeleteAfter,\n281:       },\n282:       issues,\n283:     };\n284:   }\n285: \n286:   if (!scope.tenantId) issues.push('tenantId is required for governed ingest');\n287:   if (!scope.sessionId) issues.push('sessionId is required for governed ingest');\n288:   if (!scope.userId && !scope.agentId) issues.push('userId or agentId is required for governed ingest');\n289:   if (!provenanceSource) issues.push('provenanceSource is required for governed ingest');\n290:   if (!provenanceActor) issues.push('provenanceActor is required for governed ingest');\n291:   if (deleteAfter && new Date(deleteAfter).getTime() <= new Date(governedAt).getTime()) {\n292:     issues.push('deleteAfter must be later than governedAt');\n293:   }\n294:   // H21 FIX: Require valid future deleteAfter for ephemeral retention policy\n295:   // The memory retention sweep enforces this field via memory_index.delete_after;\n296:   // keep ephemeral rows paired with a concrete timestamp for auditability.\n297:   if (retentionPolicy === 'ephemeral' && !deleteAfter) {\n298:     issues.push('deleteAfter is required for ephemeral retention policy');\n299:   }\n300: \n301:   return {\n302:     allowed: issues.length === 0,\n303:     reason: issues[0],\n304:     issues,\n305:     normalized: {\n306:       tenantId: scope.tenantId ?? '',\n307:       userId: scope.userId,\n308:       agentId: scope.agentId,\n309:       sessionId: scope.sessionId ?? '',\n310:       provenanceSource,\n311:       provenanceActor,\n312:       governedAt,\n313:       retentionPolicy,\n314:       deleteAfter,\n315:     },\n316:   };\n\n(Showing lines 227-316 of 712. Use offset=317 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":" * All ingest mutation surfaces should call `validateGovernedIngest` with their\n * available metadata before writes or job enqueue. When any scope,\n * provenance, governed timestamp, or retention field is present,\n * `provenanceActor` is mandatory so audit rows can identify the caller.\n *\n * @param input - Candidate ingest metadata.\n * @returns `true` when governance or scope metadata requires enforcement.\n */\nexport function requiresGovernedIngest(input: GovernedIngestInput): boolean {\n  const scope = normalizeScopeContext(input);\n  return Object.values(scope).some((value) => typeof value === 'string')\n    || typeof input.provenanceSource === 'string'\n    || typeof input.provenanceActor === 'string'\n    || typeof input.governedAt === 'string'\n    || (input.retentionPolicy !== 'ephemeral' && typeof input.deleteAfter === 'string');\n}\n\n/**\n * Validate governed-ingest metadata and return normalized persistence fields.\n *","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/governance/scope-governance.ts","text":" * All ingest mutation surfaces should call `validateGovernedIngest` with their\n * available metadata before writes or job enqueue. When any scope,\n * provenance, governed timestamp, or retention field is present,\n * `provenanceActor` is mandatory so audit rows can identify the caller.\n *\n * @param input - Candidate ingest metadata.\n * @returns `true` when governance or scope metadata requires enforcement.\n */\nexport function requiresGovernedIngest(input: GovernedIngestInput): boolean {\n  const scope = normalizeScopeContext(input);\n  return Object.values(scope).some((value) => typeof value === 'string')\n    || typeof input.provenanceSource === 'string'\n    || typeof input.provenanceActor === 'string'\n    || typeof input.governedAt === 'string'\n    || (input.retentionPolicy !== 'ephemeral' && typeof input.deleteAfter === 'string');\n}\n\n/**\n * Validate governed-ingest metadata and return normalized persistence fields.\n *\n * @param input - Candidate ingest metadata.\n * @returns Validation result with normalized scope, provenance, and retention data.\n */\nexport function validateGovernedIngest(input: GovernedIngestInput): GovernanceDecision {\n  const scope = normalizeScopeContext(input);\n  const issues: string[] = [];\n  const governedAt = normalizeIsoTimestamp(input.governedAt) ?? new Date().toISOString();\n  const deleteAfter = normalizeIsoTimestamp(input.deleteAfter) ?? null;\n  const retentionPolicy: RetentionPolicy = input.retentionPolicy === 'ephemeral'\n    ? input.retentionPolicy\n    : 'keep';\n  const provenanceSource = normalizeId(input.provenanceSource) ?? '';\n  const provenanceActor = normalizeId(input.provenanceActor) ?? '';\n\n  if (!requiresGovernedIngest(input)) {\n    const computedDeleteAfter = deleteAfter ?? (\n      retentionPolicy === 'ephemeral'\n        ? new Date(Date.now() + DEFAULT_EPHEMERAL_TTL_MS).toISOString()\n        : null\n    );\n    // B8: Return null instead of empty string for optional scope fields\n    // when governance is not required, to avoid persisting false-y placeholders.\n    return {\n      allowed: true,\n      normalized: {\n        tenantId: scope.tenantId || null,\n        userId: scope.userId || null,\n        agentId: scope.agentId || null,\n        sessionId: scope.sessionId || null,\n        provenanceSource: provenanceSource || null,\n        provenanceActor: provenanceActor || null,\n        governedAt,\n        retentionPolicy,\n        deleteAfter: computedDeleteAfter,\n      },\n      issues,\n    };\n  }\n\n  if (!scope.tenantId) issues.push('tenantId is required for governed ingest');\n  if (!scope.sessionId) issues.push('sessionId is required for governed ingest');\n  if (!scope.userId && !scope.agentId) issues.push('userId or agentId is required for governed ingest');\n  if (!provenanceSource) issues.push('provenanceSource is required for governed ingest');\n  if (!provenanceActor) issues.push('provenanceActor is required for governed ingest');\n  if (deleteAfter && new Date(deleteAfter).getTime() <= new Date(governedAt).getTime()) {\n    issues.push('deleteAfter must be later than governedAt');\n  }\n  // H21 FIX: Require valid future deleteAfter for ephemeral retention policy\n  // The memory retention sweep enforces this field via memory_index.delete_after;\n  // keep ephemeral rows paired with a concrete timestamp for auditability.\n  if (retentionPolicy === 'ephemeral' && !deleteAfter) {\n    issues.push('deleteAfter is required for ephemeral retention policy');\n  }\n\n  return {\n    allowed: issues.length === 0,\n    reason: issues[0],\n    issues,\n    normalized: {\n      tenantId: scope.tenantId ?? '',\n      userId: scope.userId,\n      agentId: scope.agentId,\n      sessionId: scope.sessionId ?? '',\n      provenanceSource,\n      provenanceActor,\n      governedAt,\n      retentionPolicy,\n      deleteAfter,\n    },\n  };","lineStart":227,"lineEnd":316,"totalLines":712,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/governance/scope-governance.ts","time":{"start":1780925754245,"end":1780925754249}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e3fd6258b53b2c0016a26c5396084819aa85ac8759ad7bc59"}},"id":"prt_ea772686f0010RgDZFrHaJkndV","sessionID":"ses_158903c2bffeCx3bRrBHJwKOQa","messageID":"msg_ea7725145001gYBXv1nyYYfFIp"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780925754816,"sessionID":"ses_158903c2bffeCx3bRrBHJwKOQa","part":{"id":"prt_ea7726dbd001PCnxzSduZe3k1k","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"a14296a9ba83673e389b5248f65f48c020aa9677","messageID":"msg_ea7725145001gYBXv1nyYYfFIp","sessionID":"ses_158903c2bffeCx3bRrBHJwKOQa","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":90671,"input":66525,"output":65,"reasoning":17,"cache":{"write":0,"read":24064}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780925756907,"sessionID":"ses_158903c2bffeCx3bRrBHJwKOQa","part":{"id":"prt_ea77275e7001bh68co2mYQlQDg","messageID":"msg_ea7726ed7001MUmeHDTAiglh1u","sessionID":"ses_158903c2bffeCx3bRrBHJwKOQa","snapshot":"52005c1c19dd66fc6f4c3a2548fac1953152e056","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1780925822383,"sessionID":"ses_158903c2bffeCx3bRrBHJwKOQa","part":{"id":"prt_ea772fc930017zBrhhLLqK2AQE","messageID":"msg_ea7726ed7001MUmeHDTAiglh1u","sessionID":"ses_158903c2bffeCx3bRrBHJwKOQa","type":"text","text":"## Mechanism\nOpenLTM implements provenance as a separate per-memory chain, not as frontmatter. `memory_provenance` is one-to-many, cascades with the memory, and stores `source_type`, `source_ref`, `actor`, `created_at`, and freeform `metadata`; pre-existing rows are backfilled as `legacy` (`migrations/008_add_memory_provenance.sql:1`, `migrations/008_add_memory_provenance.sql:6`, `migrations/008_add_memory_provenance.sql:21`). The actual source taxonomy is `learn`, `git-backfill`, `evaluate-session`, `import-bundle`, `user-promotion`, `janitor-rollup`, `legacy`, so the prompt’s “session” label is not a literal enum value; session is represented indirectly via `source_ref` defaulting to `sessionId` on learn (`migrations/008_add_memory_provenance.sql:9`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:377`).\n\nAudit is a separate append-oriented mutation log. `memory_audit.memory_id` is intentionally not a foreign key so audit rows survive memory deletion, and each row records `op`, required `actor`, optional `session_id`, `before_json`, `after_json`, and `created_at` (`migrations/009_add_memory_audit.sql:1`, `migrations/009_add_memory_audit.sql:6`). The initial op enum is `insert/update/forget/deprecate/supersede/redact/restore`, later rebuilt to add `archive` (`migrations/009_add_memory_audit.sql:9`, `migrations/014_update_audit_op_check.sql:6`). I did not verify SQL-level immutability triggers; the listed migrations create ordinary tables and indexes.\n\nThe DAO captures slim before/after snapshots that intentionally exclude embeddings, selecting memory metadata, lifecycle timestamps, supersession fields, workspace/agent IDs, and `created_by` (`packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:15`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:18`). `insertProvenance` and `insertAudit` are narrow helpers, while `queryAudit` filters by memory, op, session, and since, ordered newest-first with a default limit of 50 (`packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:27`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:61`).\n\nWrite paths use the audit/provenance layer selectively: duplicate reinforcement snapshots before/after and writes an `update` audit (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:321`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:334`); new learns write `created_by`, a provenance row, and an `insert` audit (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:352`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:377`); forget snapshots before deletion and writes a `forget` audit with `after_json=null` (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:606`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:611`). Janitor archive preserves full memory JSON in `memory_archive`, writes an `archive` audit, then deletes the memory (`packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/archive.ts:45`, `packages/openltm-core/src/janitor/archive.ts:53`). Audit writes are best-effort: `tryAudit` catches and logs failures without rolling back the primary mutation (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:132`).\n\nRecall can optionally carry provenance. When `includeProvenance` is set, OpenLTM batch-fetches provenance rows for all returned IDs to avoid N+1 queries and attaches them to each memory (`packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:563`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:89`). The architecture narrative frames this as fixing “what, but not where it came from” and “who/what wrote this?” gaps (`docs/03-architecture.md:710`, `docs/03-architecture.md:727`). It also sketches future replay/diff use cases from the audit log (`docs/03-architecture.md:908`).\n\n## Teachings for system-spec-kit\n- **Claim** · Add an enum-like provenance source kind per indexed memory, separate from freeform governed provenance strings. · **Evidence** · `migrations/008_add_memory_provenance.sql:9`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:377` · **Maps-to** · `memory_index` / `memory_save` / `memory_index_scan` · **Verdict** · ADAPT · **Risk** · LOW · **Confidence** · 0.90 · **Why it transfers (or not)** · Our single-user store does not need tenant-scale governance, but a stable source-kind taxonomy would make continuity/frontmatter-origin, scan backfills, imports, promotions, and janitor writes auditable without parsing prose.\n- **Claim** · Surface provenance on retrieval only when requested, using batch lookup rather than joining it into every search. · **Evidence** · `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:563`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:93` · **Maps-to** · `memory_search(includeTrace)` / `memory_context(includeTrace)` · **Verdict** · ADOPT · **Risk** · LOW · **Confidence** · 0.88 · **Why it transfers (or not)** · This complements our provenance-rich envelopes and keeps normal retrieval lean while giving debugging sessions exact source lineage.\n- **Claim** · Keep audit snapshots slim and exclude vector payloads. · **Evidence** · `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:15`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:18` · **Maps-to** · `memory_history` / mutation ledger payloads · **Verdict** · ADOPT · **Risk** · LOW · **Confidence** · 0.92 · **Why it transfers (or not)** · Our vector store is separate, so auditing metadata/text deltas without embeddings avoids huge rows and preserves replay/debug utility.\n- **Claim** · Preserve deletion audit rows independently from the deleted memory record. · **Evidence** · `migrations/009_add_memory_audit.sql:1`, `packages/openltm-core/src/dao/provenanceAudit.ts:5` · **Maps-to** · `memory_delete`, `memory_bulk_delete`, retention sweep audit · **Verdict** · ADAPT · **Risk** · MED · **Confidence** · 0.84 · **Why it transfers (or not)** · Our history/mutation ledger already covers lifecycle events, but deletion lineage should survive cleanup as a tombstone/audit class, not be treated like ordinary orphaned child data.\n- **Claim** · Do not copy fail-open auditing for governed or canonical continuity writes. · **Evidence** · `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:132`, `packages/openltm-core/src/db.ts:386` · **Maps-to** · governance audit / mutation ledger transaction policy · **Verdict** · REJECT · **Risk** · MED · **Confidence** · 0.95 · **Why it transfers (or not)** · Best-effort audit is acceptable for a lightweight plugin, but system-spec-kit already treats mutation integrity and governed ingest as stronger invariants.\n- **Claim** · Time-travel replay from audit is interesting but not the immediate delta. · **Evidence** · `docs/03-architecture.md:908`, `docs/03-architecture.md:916` · **Maps-to** · new sub-packet · **Verdict** · DEFER · **Risk** · MED · **Confidence** · 0.75 · **Why it transfers (or not)** · FSRS, causal edges, active projections, and spec-folder continuity already cover most recovery needs; replay/diff is useful only after source-kind and tombstone audit are normalized.\n\n## Negative knowledge\n- Do not copy OpenLTM’s taxonomy verbatim: its schema says `learn`, not `session`, and mixes mechanism (`learn`) with origin (`git-backfill`) and lifecycle actor (`janitor-rollup`).\n- Do not copy fail-open audit writes for canonical or governed mutations; audit loss should be explicit where compliance/debuggability matters.\n- Do not treat comments saying “append-only” as enforcement; without immutability triggers or restricted write paths, this is convention plus DAO discipline.\n- Do not duplicate our existing FSRS/causal-edge lifecycle model with OpenLTM’s lighter audit trail; use provenance/audit to explain mutations, not to replace ranking or causal lineage.\n\n## Open questions\n- Should system-spec-kit use a strict enum for `provenance_source_kind`, or a small controlled vocabulary plus freeform `provenance_source` for compatibility?\n- Should deletion audit rows live in `memory_history`, mutation ledger, or a new tombstone-only table?\n- Should `includeTrace` expose source-kind provenance by default for canonical continuity rows, or only under debug/research profiles?","time":{"start":1780925791379,"end":1780925822377},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0cd2be411d4b8179016a26c55f5d88819181766a09accf8713","phase":"final_answer"}}}}
